mindmap
  root((Enterprise Data Strategy))
    Four Pillars
      Vision — role data plays in transformation
      Governance — ownership, stewardship, accountability
      Access — speed, safety, democratization
      Quality — AI-grade completeness and consistency
    Business Alignment
      Use-case-driven investment — prioritize by impact
      Map AI initiatives to data dependencies
      Strategic dialogues with business stakeholders
    Structural Challenges
      Siloed systems — conflicting ownership
      Legacy quality — non-AI-ready data
      Poor lineage — untraceable fields
      Lack of prioritization — boiling the ocean
    Operationalization
      Embed in planning cycles and budgets
      Define roles — stewardship and accountability
      Data service models — APIs, dashboards, self-service
      Continuous improvement — retrospectives and monitoring
    Measurement
      Data maturity models — ad hoc to optimized
      Friction metrics — time spent cleaning, approval delays
      Strategic impact — ROI linked to AI performance
      Quarterly dashboards — C-suite visibility
    Culture
      Storytelling — real outcomes, human connection
      Celebrate data wins — small and large
      Data literacy — cross-functional education
      Leadership modeling — use data visibly